					</div>
					<div id="dsq-comment-body-82105" class="dsq-comment-body">
						<div id="dsq-comment-message-82105" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Quite impressive. This seems to be a turbofan, while most of jet engines this size are turbojets.</p>
<p>I can see the advantage of smaller size of a jet engine, vs. piston+prop config, but the fuel efficiency won&#8217;t be great &#8211; most of energy from the burnt up fuel will end up in the kinetic energy of the fast exhaust. For efficiency, the exhaust velocity should be roughly equal to the craft velocity and reaction mass increased adequately.</p>
</div>
					</div>
				</li>
